commit.message:
Revert "always use Python memory manager"

This reverts commit 20c7e5c3edde6cab66db0bb32ea4a98add45c0d9.

We cannot use the Python memory allocators while we also release
the GIL.

It may be possible to release the GIL until the allocators are
called though instead, but I do not know of any reason not to
use the standard libc allocators (which are thread-safe).
move version definition into C file

Merge pull request #10 from asmeurer/spelling

Fix various spelling errors

Revert "restore TypeError being raised for dictionary"

This reverts commit 5aa63e9882af5cae68e4d1fb2ddc6c2ceea97611.
restore TypeError being raised for dictionary

Merge pull request #5 from wkschwartz/py2-compile

Fix compilation error in Python 2

Merge pull request #4 from wkschwartz/iter-type-check

Teach (iter)solve to take generic iterables of iterables as clauses argument
Test non-list iterable arguments on itersolve

Fix compilation error in Python 2

Python 2's module init function is void so cannot return even NULL whereas
Python 3's must return a pointer (apparently).
Add a test to ensure a bad iterator won't segfault pycosat.c's add_clauses

Teach solve/itersolve to accept clauses as general iterables

Commit fdf54a86bfe201fe5a465354b7b19a03f62471f4 taught them to accept the list
of lists that represented clauses as any iterable of lists. Now it can be any
iterable of any iterables.

Remove redundant setting of TypeError when clauses isn't an iterator

According to the CPython API, PyObject_GetIter sets a TypeError without needing
it to be set again by the calling code.
